01/11/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Court of BiH sentenced a former Republika Srpska (RS) Army commander to 22 years in prison for war crimes Friday (October 30th). Predrag Kujundzic was found guilty of murder, sexual slavery, inhuman treatment and persecution of Bosnian and Croat civilians in Doboi, during the 1992-1995 conflict. He may appeal the verdict. (RTRS, Fena, BHRT, Dnevni Avaz, Reuters, AFP, AP, Beta, B92 - 30/10/09)
